-- Tata Steel to Raise $2 Billion in Share Sale to Fund Expansion: Chronicle
-- Suprotip Ghosh
-- 2010-07-14T02:14:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-14/tata-steel-to-raise-2-billion-in-share-sale-to-fund-expansion-chronicle.html

          
          
             Tata Steel Ltd., India’s largest
producer of alloy, will raise $2 billion by issuing fresh equity
in the coming three months to finance its expansion
projects in India and abroad. The money will be raised in three
parts and the company is in the process of finalizing a lead
arranger for the offering, the Financial Chronicle reported,
citing a banker it didn’t identify.  
